2018-04-24.description: FoodOn (http://foodon.org) is a consortium-driven project to build a comprehensive and easily accessible global farm-to-fork ontology about food, that accurately and consistently describes foods commonly known in cultures from around the world.
2018-04-24.title: Food Ontology

2018-04-24.description: The Genomic Epidemiology Ontology aims to provide a comprehensive controlled vocabulary for infectious disease surveillance and outbreak investigations. It is an application ontology that draws on many other ontologies including anatomy, taxonomy, disease, symptoms, environment and food types.
2018-04-24.title: Genomic Epidemiology Ontology
